<reference id="dita" xml:lang="en-us">
   <title>
      <keyword>dita</keyword>
   </title>
   <shortdesc>The &lt;<keyword>dita</keyword>&gt; element provides a top-level container
for multiple topics when you create documents using the ditabase DTD. The
&lt;<keyword>dita</keyword>&gt; element lets you create any sequence of concept,
task, and reference topics, and the ditabase DTD lets you further nest these
topic types inside each other. The &lt;<keyword>dita</keyword>&gt; element has
no particular output implications; it simply allows you to create multiple
topics of different types at the same level in a single document.</shortdesc>
   <prolog>
      <metadata>
         <keywords>
            <indexterm>dita</indexterm>
            <indexterm>Compound
topics</indexterm>
         </keywords>
      </metadata>
   </prolog>
   <refbody>
      <refsyn>
         <title>Contained by</title>No parent content.</refsyn>
      <refsyn>
         <title>Contains</title>
         <xref href="topic.xml">topic</xref> or <xref href="concept.xml">concept</xref> or <xref href="task.xml">task</xref> or <xref href="reference.xml">reference</xref>
      </refsyn>
      <section>
         <title>Attributes</title>
         <simpletable relcolwidth="2* 3* 1* 1* 1*" id="dita_attr">
            <sthead>
               <stentry>Name</stentry>
               <stentry>Description</stentry>
               <stentry>Data Type</stentry>
               <stentry>Default Value</stentry>
               <stentry>Required?</stentry>
            </sthead>
            <strow conref="commonLRdefs.xml#commonLRdefs/global-atts">
               <stentry/>
               <stentry/>
               <stentry/>
               <stentry/>
               <stentry/>
            </strow>
         </simpletable>
      </section>
      <example>
         <pre>&lt;dita&gt;
  &lt;concept id="batintro"&gt;...&lt;/concept&gt;
  &lt;reference id="batparts"&gt;...&lt;/reference&gt;
  &lt;task id="batfeeding"&gt;...&lt;/task&gt;
  &lt;task id="battraining"&gt;...&lt;/task&gt;
  &lt;task id="batcleanup"&gt;...&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;/dita&gt;</pre>
      </example>
   </refbody>
